{% extends "../layouts/base.njk" %}

{% block title %}Android to PC File Transfer Free – No USB, No App | Tranzo{% endblock %}
{% block metaDesc %}Transfer files from Android to PC without USB cable, Bluetooth, or any app install. Use Tranzo's free WebRTC browser-based transfer over Wi-Fi or internet.{% endblock %}
{% block canonical %}<link rel="canonical" href="{{ siteUrl }}/android-to-pc-file-transfer" />{% endblock %}
{% block ogTitle %}Android to PC File Transfer Free – No USB | Tranzo{% endblock %}
{% block ogUrl %}{{ siteUrl }}/android-to-pc-file-transfer{% endblock %}

{% block adTop %}
<div class="container-lg pt-3">
  <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-leaderboard">
    <iframe src="about:blank" title="Advertisement" aria-label="Advertisement" scrolling="no"></iframe>
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<main class="content-page">
  <div class="container-lg">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">

        <div class="page-eyebrow">&#128241; Android → PC</div>
        <h1>Android to PC File Transfer <span class="grad">Without USB</span></h1>
        <p class="lead">Send photos, videos, and files from your Android phone to any PC instantly — no cable, no Bluetooth, no app install. Just a browser on both devices.</p>

        <div class="d-flex gap-3 mb-5 flex-wrap">
          <a href="/" class="btn-em" style="text-decoration:none;">Transfer Now &#9889;</a>
          <a href="/faq" class="btn-ghost" style="text-decoration:none;">FAQ</a>
        </div>

        <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-rect mb-4">
          <iframe src="about:blank" title="Advertisement" aria-label="Advertisement" scrolling="no"></iframe>
        </div>

        <h2>Step-by-Step: Android to PC</h2>

        <div class="info-card mb-3">
          <div class="d-flex gap-3">
            <div style="width:32px;height:32px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--em);color:#fff;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:14px;flex-shrink:0;">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="margin-top:0;">On your PC — Create a Room</h3>
              <p class="mb-0">Open <a href="/">{{ siteUrl | replace("https://", "") }}</a> in your PC browser (Chrome, Firefox, or Edge). Enter a name and click <strong>Create</strong>. A share link and QR code appear.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card mb-3">
          <div class="d-flex gap-3">
            <div style="width:32px;height:32px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--em);color:#fff;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:14px;flex-shrink:0;">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="margin-top:0;">On your Android — Scan the QR Code</h3>
              <p class="mb-0">Open Chrome on your Android phone. Go to <a href="/">{{ siteUrl | replace("https://", "") }}</a> and tap <strong>Scan QR to join</strong>. Point your camera at the QR code on the PC screen. You'll join the room instantly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card mb-3">
          <div class="d-flex gap-3">
            <div style="width:32px;height:32px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--amb);color:#fff;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:14px;flex-shrink:0;">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="margin-top:0;">On Android — Pick Your Files</h3>
              <p class="mb-0">Tap the drop zone or the file area to open the Android file picker or gallery. Select photos, videos, or any files. Tranzo handles the connection recovery if Chrome briefly suspends while the picker is open.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card mb-4">
          <div class="d-flex gap-3">
            <div style="width:32px;height:32px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--amb);color:#fff;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:14px;flex-shrink:0;">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="margin-top:0;">On PC — Accept and Download</h3>
              <p class="mb-0">Your PC shows an incoming file modal. Click <strong>Accept &amp; Save</strong>. The file transfers directly from Android to PC at full speed. No intermediate upload, no waiting.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Mid-page ad -->
        <div class="ad-slot ad-slot-banner my-4">
          <iframe src="about:blank" title="Advertisement" aria-label="Advertisement" scrolling="no"></iframe>
        </div>

        <h2>Sending from PC to Android</h2>
        <p>The process works both ways. Create the room on your Android, share the QR code with your PC, then drag and drop files from the PC. The Android download directory receives the file automatically.</p>

        <h2>Tips for the Best Experience</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Same Wi-Fi = fastest speed.</strong> When both devices are on the same network, Tranzo connects directly over LAN (no internet hops) and can reach 50–100 MB/s.</li>
          <li><strong>Keep Chrome in foreground</strong> while transferring large files on Android to prevent aggressive battery management from suspending the tab.</li>
          <li><strong>Use QR code scanning</strong> — it's faster than typing the room URL on a phone keyboard.</li>
          <li><strong>Multiple files at once</strong> — select multiple files from the Android gallery in a single picker session.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why Not Use Bluetooth or USB?</h2>
        <p>Bluetooth tops out around 2–3 MB/s and requires pairing. USB requires a cable and sometimes drivers. Tranzo over Wi-Fi is dramatically faster than both, requires zero hardware, and works even when the devices are in different buildings or countries.</p>

        <div class="d-flex gap-3 mt-4">
          <a href="/" class="btn-em" style="text-decoration:none;">Transfer Android to PC Now &#9889;</a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
{% endblock %}
